Delegate Seminar:
The seminar I would like to present is about the vision of science in Latin America and why I felt the need to create the first Youth Association for Science and Technology. Even in one of the most developed countries, Chile, there are still many schools with limited access to science. This is exactly what we want to change—these barriers are what we aim to break down with AJCT. We want to ensure that young people have the access to science they desire and the support they need. Our goal is to expand this initiative from Chile to Latin America. I also want to hear the voices of people from the United States and other parts of the world to learn what advice they can offer and how they have improved access to science in their own communities. This seminar will address the vision we have in Latin America about science, present the progress we’ve made with this project, and explore what we can continue to achieve. We hope to inspire others to join the project and see how they can contribute to their own communities.
